The paper focuses on face detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves the use of convolutional neural networks (cs.AI) and multi-scale information (cs.MM) to improve performance. The approach also incorporates contextual reasoning (cs.IR) inspired by the human vision system. Finally, the paper presents experimental results and compares its approach to other state-of-the-art methods, which is a common practice in machine learning (cs.LG).
